Interface IImageModel

All Known Implementing Classes:
ImageModel
public interface IImageModel
Defines the behavior of an image model for managing image data and operations. Provides methods for reading, writing, and exporting images, as well as retrieving image metadata.

    • readImage

      void readImage(String path) throws IOException, IllegalAccessException
      Reads an image from the specified file path.
      Parameters:
      path - the path of the image file to read
      Throws:
      IOException - if there is an error reading the file
      IllegalAccessException - if access to the file is denied

    • writeImage

      void writeImage(String path) throws IOException, IllegalAccessException
      Writes the current image to the specified file path.
      Parameters:
      path - the path where the image will be saved
      Throws:
      IOException - if there is an error writing the file
      IllegalAccessException - if access to the file writer is inaccessible

    • getImageName

      String getImageName()
      Retrieves the name of the current image file.
      Returns:
      a String representing the name of the image file

    • getImagePixels

      long[][] getImagePixels()
      Retrieves the pixel data of the current image.
      Returns:
      a 2D array of long values representing the ARGB pixels of the image

    • getSupportedExtensions

      List<String> getSupportedExtensions()
      Retrieves the list of supported file extensions for images.
      Returns:
      a List of String containing the supported file extensions

    • export

      void export(String extension, String path) throws IOException, IllegalAccessException
      Exports the current image to the specified file path with the given file extension.
      Parameters:
      extension - the file extension to use for the exported image
      path - the path where the image will be exported
      Throws:
      IOException - if there is an error exporting the file
      IllegalAccessException - if access to the file writer is inaccessible
